HEADWORD: Louis dor
<hw>Lou"is d'or`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., gold
louis.]</ety> <def>Formerly, a gold coin of France nominally worth
twenty shillings sterling, but of varying value; -- first struck in
1640.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

